EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to employment; establishing the Nevada State
Service Corps as a program within the Department of
Administration; requiring the Department to develop and
oversee the Nevada State Service Corps; and providing
other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law: (1) requires the Human Resources Commission to adopt
2 regulations for the certification of qualified persons for temporary service with this
3 State; and (2) authorizes an agency to appoint persons temporarily for less than 160
4 cumulative hours, with certain exceptions, during any calendar year without regard
5 to such regulations. (NRS 284.325) Section 1 of this bill establishes the Nevada
6 State Service Corps as a program within the Department of Administration and
7 requires the Department to develop and oversee the Nevada State Service Corps to
8 provide for the placement and mentoring of recent graduates of the Nevada System
9 of Higher Education for service in certain positions with the Executive Department
10 of the State Government. Section 1 requires the Department to recruit certain
11 students to participate in the Nevada State Service Corps. Section 1 further requires
12 the Legislative Commission to appoint a legislator to serve as an advisor to the
13 participants, promote the benefits of state service and provide encouragement to the
14 participants.
15 Section 2 of this bill provides that a position in the classified service with the
16 Nevada State Service Corps may be filled by an appointing authority without
17 competitive evaluation.
18 Section 3 of this bill provides that employment for service with the Nevada
19 State Service Corps is an exception to the limitation on the number of hours an
20 agency may appoint a person for temporary service without regard to the
21 regulations adopted by the Human Resources Commission.
