THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 284 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. The Nevada State Service Corps is hereby established as a
4 program within the Department of Administration.
5 2. The Department shall develop and oversee the Nevada
6 State Service Corps to provide for the placement and mentoring of
7 recent graduates of the Nevada System of Higher Education for
8 service in positions with the Executive Department of the State
9 Government.
10 3. In overseeing the Nevada State Service Corps, the
11 Department shall recruit students who are graduating or
12 graduated within the immediately preceding year from the Nevada
13 System of Higher Education to participate in the Nevada State
14 Service Corps.
15 4. The Director of the Department shall determine the
16 number of students who may participate in the Nevada State
17 Service Corps in each year.
18 5. The Legislative Commission shall appoint a legislator to
19 serve as an advisor to participants in the Nevada State Service
20 Corps, promote the benefits of state service and provide
21 encouragement to the participants. A legislator appointed
22 pursuant to this subsection serves without compensation and is not
23 entitled to the per diem and travel expenses provided for state
24 officers and employees generally.
25 6. The Director of the Department may:
26 (a) Apply for and receive gifts, grants, donations and bequests
27 to carry out the provisions of this section; and
28 (b) Adopt regulations to carry out the provisions of this
29 section.
30 Sec. 2. NRS 284.305 is hereby amended to read as follows:
31 284.305 1. Except as otherwise provided in subsection 2,
32 positions in the classified service may be filled by an appointing
33 authority without competitive evaluation only as provided in NRS
34 284.155, 284.300, 284.307, 284.308, 284.309, 284.310, 284.315,
35 284.320, 284.325, 284.327, 284.330, 284.375 and 284.3775 [.] and
36 section 1 of this act.
37 2. The Commission may adopt regulations which provide for
38 filling positions in the classified service without competitive
39 evaluation in cases involving:
40 (a) The appointment of a current employee with a disability to a
41 position at or below the grade of his or her position if the employee
