6 reclassification or a permanent partial disability arising out of and in
7 the course of the employment of the current or former employee; or
8 (d) The reappointment of a current employee.
9 Sec. 3. NRS 284.325 is hereby amended to read as follows:
10 284.325 1. The Commission shall adopt regulations not
11 inconsistent with this section for the certification of qualified
12 persons for temporary service.
13 2. Except as otherwise provided in subsection 3, temporary
14 positions which occur, terminate or recur periodically must be filled
15 by certification in accordance with the regulations adopted by the
16 Commission.
17 3. An agency may appoint persons temporarily for less than
18 160 cumulative hours during any calendar year without regard to the
19 regulations adopted by the Commission pursuant to subsection 1.
20 4. The limitation on hours set forth in subsection 3 does not
21 apply to temporary or part-time service by:
22 (a) A pupil attending the pupil’s last 2 years of high school;
23 (b) A student employed by the college or university the student
24 attends;
25 (c) A person certified for temporary service in accordance with
26 NRS 284.327;
27 (d) An employee of an events center, museum or research center
28 of the Nevada System of Higher Education;
29 (e) A person employed by the Nevada System of Higher
30 Education in a temporary position which recurs periodically for the
31 registration of students; [or]
32 (f) A person employed by the Nevada System of Higher
33 Education to provide such assistance to a student with a disability or
34 to a student with an identified academic disadvantage as it
35 determines is necessary for the academic success of the student,
36 including, without limitation, a person employed as a tutor, note
37 taker, reader, sign interpreter or test proctor [.] ; or
38 (g) A person employed for service with the Nevada State
39 Service Corps established pursuant to section 1 of this act.
40 5. The acceptance or refusal by an eligible person of a
41 temporary appointment does not affect the person’s standing on the
42 register for permanent employment, nor may the period of
43 temporary service be counted as part of the probationary period in
44 case of subsequent appointment to a permanent position.
